Oct 24 2009 	Lovely hotel and fantastic location for tourists	Stayed here for 4 nights as part of a 2 centre holiday to California. The main purpose of visiting San Francisco was to see all the sights that this city has to offer and this hotel is perfectly located to allow for this. The hotel is a couple of streets back from the Wharf (5-10 mins walk on foot). Our room was on the front overlooking the pool, and was overlooked hotels on the other side of the road, meaning it was nice and quiet. There were bars and places to eat all within easy reach. We could also see the top of the Transamerica Pyramid from the window. The room was spacious and nicely decorated. One thing I liked about the hotel was the free internet access, as a lot of hotels charge for this. There is a pay phone in reception and due to the time difference, I found it was quite cheap to call back to the UK from there in the evening (California time).The staff were also good. I would definitely stay here again, and hope to return to San Francisco at some point in the future - it's a fantastic city.	
