Jul 10 2009 	Excellent Location Be aware of the Plus 26% tax in San Francisco	We did not know about the 26% tax that the city of San Francisco applies to all guests in hotel rooms. So it adds to the price quoted.( Not the Hotels fault)The location of this hotel is close to everything on Fishermans Wharf, but allow a brisk 25 minute walk to Pier 33 and the ferry to Alcatraz.It is a good idea to book online for the trip to alcatraz beforehand, as tickets sell fast and up to a week ahead.The room we had was on the business level ( 5th floor) and room 508)It was very spacious and the king size bed very comfortable, fridge and microwave included.The are two buildings at the Holiday Inn, try and get a room in the main building.There is an ATM at the Hotel (limit $200) and free wireless internet in the rooms.Also a business centre with Internet, printer etc on the 5th floor, but you need nto be staying on the 5th to use it.The hotel staff are very polite and most helpful. The cable car to the city is just around the corner and the queues not too bad.Coming back is a different story, be prepared for a 30 minute wait as the queues are long. The trip is $5 each way, or a day pass for $11 per person.One day we caught a taxi back rather than line up and the difference in cost was $3.I would recommend this hotel to all, thank you to the Staff at the Holiday Inn	
