Jul 2 2009 	Terrific Location Comfortable Friendly 	I chose this hotel after DAYS of discussions with a travel agent friend and after reviewing maps of San Francisco hotels/neighborhoods until my eyes crossed. Package prices via Priceline were so similar, I didn't want to miss staying at a high-end 5* hotel when it was only dollars more per night. In the end, I chose this Holiday Inn for several key reasons:Free Wifi: The prices I read for in-room Wifi at some other hotels were amazingly expensive and I didn't want to spend any of my vacation money that way.Location: You're three blocks from Fisherman's Wharf, a few blocks from the the trolley cars, and there's a bus stop just outside of the hotel door on the street. Even though you are in the heart of the tourist area, we never heard a noise except for the morning garbage truck previously mentioned in other reviews - and after the first morning, we never heard it again.Fridge at no charge: The hotel provided a free small refrigerator as we needed it for medication. The fridge was delivered to the room and working within five minutes of our check-in.Large room: We stayed on the 4th floor and the room was huge. It featured a king-size bed, lovely sofa-bed, desk, two nightstands, a dresser, and an entry hall closet area.Other noteworthy items: free in-room safe, coffeemaker &amp; coffee, pool, nice toiletries, thick towels (and plenty of them), iron and ironing board, hairdryer, and a plush bed we just wanted to sink into.We rented a car for one day (to see Napa Valley &amp; Muir Woods) and because of the expensive hotel parking fee, we returned the vehicle that night instead of paying to park it at the hotel. If you must have your own vehicle and must park it at the hotel, be prepared for the price, because it is going to cost you some money. Thankfully mass transit is a breeze in San Francisco, so we did not need a car to see the city.One day house-keeping forgot to replenish our coffee supply so on our way out, I mentioned it to the woman at the restaurant/bakery counter in the lobby, and she gave both of us free Starbucks. That's the kind of customer service that makes a huge difference! The concierge was friendly when arranging our transportation to the airport for the return flight and he even matched the price of a competitor. Every employee we met was friendly and willing to assist so we have no personnel complaints at all!You can stay at more expensive hotels that charge for every little thing and you can stay at less expensive hotels that may give you pause upon arrival. We're happy that we stayed where we did b/c it was comfortable, clean, and fell nicely in the middle of the hundreds of San Francisco hotels at which I looked.	
