Jun 26 2009 	Great location and price rest is just average	Stayed here with husband and children for three nights. The location was great, only short walk to all the piers. Was also within walking distance of Little Italy, Ghirardelli Square, and Chinatown. When booking our room we were told it would have two queen beds and a sofa. Upon arrival, we were disappointed to find two double beds and no sofa. The room was also small for a family, and would have been better suited to two people. Our room was across the street from the main section, on Beach St. It was extremely noisy at night. The cable cars, buses, and people were right under our window which made it hard to fall asleep, and got us up early. We are from a major city so we are used to loud noise, but this was ridiculous. Also, the bath towels always had a weird smell to them, even though we got fresh ones everyday. Parking was expensive but we were aware of that beforehand. We were not in the room often and only used it to sleep and for a quick rest stop. All in all, you get what you pay for. This hotel really does have a great location, and we got a pretty good price, especially for San Francisco.	
Jun 23 2009 	Quite possibly the best mainstream hotel I have ever stayed in	On first review, it’s a Holiday Inn… nothing special, nothing spectacular, just a Holiday Inn. However, it is far, far more than this. The Hotel is located very centrally in Fishermans Wharf, which is the main touristy area, with plenty of restaurants and bars to choose from. Also, it’s about a 10 minute walk to the Italian district and 20 minutes to china town, with lots of fantastic restaurants. Furthermore, it’s about a 1 minute walk to Denny’s (within the second building) and Starbucks, so you don’t have to pay silly money for the hotels breakfast.The hotel itself is split into two, a main building with reception on Columbus Avenue, and a second building which we stayed in on Beach Street, again with a small reception. Probably best to phone the hotel first to find out which building you will be in as there is quite a walk between the two. Not easy with heavy cases.The rooms are large, mine had a king sized bed, sofa and desk, as well as a large bathroom. They are very well decorated, the bedding is simple &amp; clean and the towels plentiful. Security is good with lifts (or elevators) locked by room key, one-way emergency exits and safes in each room. One issue if you drive there is parking, it’s really, really expensive!I would definitely recommend this hotel to anybody who wants to go to San Francisco for a vacation or even a business trip.	
