Mar 24 2009 	Location Fabulous and plan to stay here again.	The location of this hotel cannot be beaten being just a couple of minutes walk from fisherman's wharf, Pier 39 and access to sight-seeing tours etc. Also close by are bus stops, tram stops and the cable car so its easy to get just about anywhere in San Francisco without having a car. We were glad we did not hire one as parking is expensive, being $43 dollars a night and really it is so easy to get about San Francisco on foot if you can get there without a car then I would. We had a room with a king bed on the fourth (top) floor and the room was light, bright and spacious and included a sofa which was great for relaxing and reading about where we had been during the day. We had a ten night stay and never felt cramped or fed up with the room. The hanging wardrobe space was a little tight but there were plenty of other drawers and cupboards to accomodate our clothes. The decor would not be to everyone's taste as it is contemporary and a little quirky but we found it refreshingly pleasant. We thoroughly enjoyed watching the sun set on the city through our bedroom window in the evening. The bathroom was a bit on the small side but perfectly adequate and the maid service was excellent; our rooms being cleaned relatively early in the morning as soon as we departed and we never returned during the day to an unmade bed. We must admit we found the buffet breakfast a bit steep at $19.95 a person (plus tax) but for the odd couple of occasions we treated ourselves and if you breakfast late and take your fill then lunch could easily be skipped. The service in the breakfast room was pleasant and attentive. We did notice that many people enquired about breakfast but were not willing to pay the price and to be honest I don't blame them but don't let this be a reason not to stay here as there are plenty of other eateries close by and, perhaps best of all, there is a Safeway supermarket opposite where we bought our own croissants at a fraction of the price and breakfasted in our room. There is also a good deli at Safeway where you can buy pretty much all your dietary requirements if your budget is tight. (Just take some cutlery, and a couple of bowls for your cornflakes!). We did not have much interaction with the staff but only because we had no cause for complaint or query as all our needs had been pretty much catered for without a need to raise them. We found the check in/check out staff were perhaps slightly more formal than at some hotels but they were perfectly polite and attentive so no complaint there. There is unfortunately quite a bit of traffic noise early in the morning but after a couple of days this didn't even wake us and to be honest all the other pro's make up for this. I really, really hope we are able to get back to San Franciscio if we do we will definitely stay at The Sheraton	
