Mar 17 2009 	Great Value Good Rooms and Extremely Convenient! Free Wi-Fi too!	I booked this room from 2/18-2/23 and chose this hotel based upon previous reviews. I found this to be the best value at $72, before taxes and fees in comparison to surrounding accommodations (exclusive of parking fees, since we didn't rent a car, but you really don't need one.) I recommend to checking the hotel website directly first, then AAA (if you have a membership), and then finally discount sites such as Orbitz. On this trip (my second visit to SFO), I booked with Orbitz.There are three buildings within two blocks of one another. Two of them belong to Holiday Inn at Fisherman's Wharf and the other is Holiday Inn EXPRESS at Fisherman's Wharf, which is not owned by the same management. I am reviewing for Holiday Inn at Fisherman's Wharf on 1300 Columbus Ave, although I didn't stay at the main building. It is so convenient!!! Only a block away from Fisherman's Wharf. There is a Walgreens that is open until midnight across the street, and you can have an inexpensive breakfast at Boudin's about three blocks away! Everything is within walking distance.Upon arrival at nearly 10pm, I was offered a complimentary upgrade in the main building with the front desk. However, I declined as I required two double beds. So, I had to stay at the other building around the corner, and down the block where Denny's is located. (This is what a previous review called &quot;The Annex&quot;, but when I asked front desk, if they are sending me to &quot;The Annex&quot;, the didn't know what I was talking about.) I read bad reviews about this building, but it really isn't bad at all. Well, except for the grease smell every time you use the Denny entrance to get to the elevators. There is no front desk service, and no concierge on duty, but you are welcomed to the same services as the main building. (Such as complimentary newspapers to be picked up at the check-in counter.) You can only access your room from the lobby elevators, which requires a valid room key. Denny is open 24hrs, which is great for midnight cravings. They even allow you to &quot;take-out&quot; back to your room. There is NO FREE BREAKFAST in the main building, as I have read in previous postings. However, a breakfast buffet is available for $15pp, which includes eggs, sausages, and continental breakfast items.I was very surprised by the size of the rooms, and the two queen beds in this hi-rise building. There isn't much of view from my floor, but it is higher than the main building. On my previous trip, I stayed at the Palace for $169 in 2005. The room at the Holiday Inn is definitely bigger. All you are paying for is the ambiance, service, and decor at the Palace. The beds are very comfortable at the Holiday Inn. We all agreed on that! The staff is friendly, and you only see them about once or twice a day. This building is very quiet. A computer is available on one of the floors with 24hr internet access and unlimited free printing. But you don't need it, if you bring your laptop because there is free Wi-Fi in the rooms. There is even a 24hr laundry area on the floor! There are a few muni buses in the area that brings you to basically any attraction. The 31 runs along Stockton, through Chinatown, and into Downtown. This bus can connect to either the BART or CalTrain. Then, there is the F-Line that runs through Fisherman's Wharf, Embarcado, and Downtown. The F-Line is in front of Walgreens, which is across the street. There is also the 47 which goes across town to Haight &amp; Ashbury area, and Cowhow. We were able to walk to Ghiradelli, Lombard St, Pier 39 and Alcatraz tours a few more piers down.If you are looking for a three star accommodation, with great value, then this is the place to stay. There is a charge for an extra person in the room, but no one ever checks. You can easily have four adults stay in one room, in the building with Denny's because there is no front desk person monitoring. I highly recommend this hotel for families on a budget, but still want a clean and comfortable environment.	
