Sep 1 2005	Not bad great location	A quick warning before I start the review.....if your room is in the annex building, use a bellman ! Getting to the other building includes walking out on to the street in front of the hotel and a good 300 yard walk down a busy road. I lost count of the number of people I saw lugging heavy cases, clearly underestimating how far apart the entrances to the 2 separate buildings are.We spent 2 nights in the annex building in August 2005. The room was satisfactory (2 queen size beds) although the decoration was a bit dated. It was kept clean though and we were impressed by the friendly maid service who went out of her way on a few occasions. There is a 24 hour Dennys in the lobby of the annex, where service was dreadfully slow in the mornings when it gets busy. We had a 30 minute wait for food which was not good when you only have a day and a half in the City and want to get out and see some sights. The famous Lombard Street crooked street is walkable too, although the hill you walk up to get there is VERY steep.I can't fault the location of the hotel which was in easy walking distance of Fishermans Wharf, Alcatraz Ferry, Cable car turnaround (where you could catch a cable car all the way into downtown area), The Cannery etc etc. A cab from downtown back to the hotel cost about $9 - worth getting as he tool us speedily over Russian Hill, reminding us of the classic Steve McQueen car chase!We didn't use the pool or main restaurant, but generally we were happy with the hotel. Not exceptional, but functional and close to the action. One last word of warning though - if you bring your car, you will get charged $32 per day which seems to be a common charge in this city. Parking is a nightmare in SF and driving is not too pleasurable either, so its a good idea to leave your car out of the city if you can. We booked our stay through a travel agent and got our parking charge waived, but the guy in front of me checking in went pale when they told him the car park charge!	
Aug 27 2005	Great Location - Walk almost anywhere	Holiday Inn at the Wharf is close to many attractions. We took our two boys. Ghirardelli Square, the Cannery, the Wharf, Ferry Docks for Alcatraz, the Hyde Cable Car line, shopping! August was a crowded month. But we seemed to get everything on the MUST SEE and DO list checked off. Hotel is older, but well located and recently remodeled. Our room was clean and the maid service was GREAT. Pool is a bit small, and were the hotel to add a jacuzzi spa we would definitely go back. Food is pricy at the hotel and at the Denny's in the annex across the street, but the entire city is expensive when it comes to meal time. Lots of clean towels, sofa bed could use a replacement matress, but that is where the two kids slept and they could have cared less. No view from our room (just a purple and blue wall from the building accross the alley but Who wants to sit in a room with the action all about you outside? ) - when we checked in, we asked to be upgraded from a room with two doubles to a king plus pull out queen and the staff graciously accomodated our request. Lot's of families with kids stay here, so there can be a bit of playful noise about. If you are on a honeymoon or want a quiet romantic weekend, you should probably not stay here.	
